---
// src/components/FrictionWarningBanner.astro
---
<div class="border border-amber-200/50 dark:border-amber-900/30 bg-amber-50/20 dark:bg-amber-950/10 rounded-lg p-3.5 flex items-start gap-3 transition-colors duration-300">
  <!-- Info Circle SVG Icon -->
  <div class="flex-shrink-0 mt-0.5 text-amber-600 dark:text-amber-500">
    <svg class="w-4 h-4" fill="none" viewBox="0 0 24 24" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2">
      <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" d="M12 9v2m0 4h.01m-6.938 4h13.856c1.54 0 2.502-1.667 1.732-3L13.732 4c-.77-1.333-2.694-1.333-3.464 0L3.34 16c-.77 1.333.192 3 1.732 3z" />
    </svg>
  </div>
  
  <!-- Content area -->
  <div class="space-y-1">
    <span class="block font-mono text-[9px] uppercase tracking-widest text-amber-800 dark:text-amber-400 font-semibold transition-colors">
      Travel Compliance Advisory
    </span>
    <p class="font-sans text-[11px] text-zinc-650 dark:text-zinc-405 leading-relaxed transition-colors">
      Passport validity criteria—such as the <strong>6-month remaining rule</strong> and blank visa page requirements—apply <strong>independently</strong> of visa approvals. Because operating airlines verify physical travel credentials at check-in using the official <strong>Timatic</strong> database, passengers must ensure passport compliance and are strongly urged to cross-reference search findings directly with official embassy portals before booking flights.
    </p>
  </div>
</div>
